    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6578" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ξεῖνος</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">strange,
            foreign</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 24.302</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 7.32</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ξεῖνε πάτερ</span>, ‘sir stranger’;
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">stranger, guest, guest - friend;</span> the relation of
          guest - friend existed from the time when <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ζεινήια</span> were exchanged as tokens and pledges; hence
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πατρώιος ξεῖνος</span>, ‘hereditary
          friend,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 6.215</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
